  "pride_metadata": {
    "project": {
      "accession": "PXD031807",
      "title": "S-nitrosylation of p53 in A375 cells",
      "additionalAttributes": [],
      "projectDescription": "Nitric oxide (NO) is a pleiotropic signaling molecule that affects numerous biological functions. One unique posttranslational modification of proteins by NO is termed S-nitrosylation (SNO), but the role in modulating key proteins\u2019 function in melanoma has not been fully characterized. In the present study, by conducting the biotin switch assay and mass spectrometry, we confirmed that p53 was S-nitrosylated under nitrosative stress. Further proteomic characterization showed that Cys242, Cys275, and Cys277 were S-nitrosylated in A375 cells treated with 100 \u00b5M GSNO.",
      "sampleProcessingProtocol": "For the detection of S-nitrosylated proteins after biotin switch assay, 100 \u00b5g of biotin-labeled proteins were diluted in 500 \u00b5L wash buffer (S-Nitrosylation Wash Buffer, Item No. 10006519, Cayman Chemical) and resuspended in 70 \u00b5L of High-capacity streptavidin agarose resin (UBPBio, P3070-5), which was previously washed two times with 1X PBS. After incubation for one hour at room temperature, the mixtures were centrifuged, and the supernatant was discarded. The harvested pellets were washed three times with 1X PBS. Then, 50 \u00b5L of Laemmli buffer (bioPLUS Chemicals) with 5 % \u03b2-mercaptoethanol (Acros Organics) were added to each sample and boiled for 10 min at 100 \u02daC to detached biotinylated proteins derived from S-nitrosylated protein from resin. The samples were centrifuged for the separation and the supernatants were collected for the molecular analyses.  The melanoma protein samples derived from A375 cells treated with NO donors were subjected to the biotin switch assay. Then the biotinylated proteins were separated by native PAGE gels. After traditional Coomassie blue staining, the protein bands close to 53 kDa were excised and purified from the gels. The gels were further distained with gel distain solution followed by enzymatic digestion and peptides extraction, based on the protocol described in the previous report (https://doi.org/10.1002/0471142727.mb1025s88).",
      "dataProcessingProtocol": "The peptides were further analyzed by LC/MS/MS on an LTQ-Orbitrap-XL mass spectrometer (Thermo Fisher) interfaced with an Eksigent Nano-LC-Ultra- 2D plus CHiPLC Nanoflex system (AB SCIEX). The reverse-phase C18 chromatographic separation of peptides were carried on a ChromXP C18-CL column. The raw data files were processed to generate a Mascot Generic Format with Mascot Distiller and searched against the SwissProt_2012_01 (Human) database using the licensed Mascot search engine v2.3.02 (Matrix Science). The spectra were also searched against the decoy database using a target false discovery rate (FDR) of 1 % for strict and 5 % for relaxed conditions. Based on the S-nitrosylated protein detection kit (Cayman Chemical, Item no. 10006518), the S-nitrosylated modification was converted into the adduct of maleimide-PEO2-biotin on related cysteine residues.",
      "projectTags": [],
      "keywords": [
        "A375",
        "Mass spectrometry",
        "S-nitrosylation",
        "P53",
        "Melanoma cells"
      ],
